The paper proposes a new programming model for shared memory parallelism that enforces determinism. This topic falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the implementation of the programming model, which involves language constructs and runtime systems, making it relevant to Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Operating Systems (cs.OS). The paper also mentions the use of synchronization abstractions, which is relevant to Architecture (cs.AR). Finally, the paper proposes a programming model that is easy to understand and use, which is relevant to Software Engineering (cs.SE).
